<p>The design career path of Raul Barbieri starts well before his arrival in Rexite. During his studies he was working at Sottsass’ studio, one of the leading icons of 70’s Italian design, where he was involved with the improvement of Olivetti’s projects.</p>

<p>Rino Pirovano met Raul Barbieri during a meeting with a company that manufactured lamps: Pirovano provided them some of the components, while Barbieri was their designer. As soon as Raul found out about Rino Pirovano and Boschet’s talent in making molds, molding plastic, and cutting metal, he became extremely passionate about their works and offered them a partnership. Raul<strong> began to design specific items that could be easily produced by Pirovano and Boschet.</strong></p>

<p>The improvement of technique and the knowledge of metal production, as well as metal and plastic molding, led the young partners to an awareness of their technical and productive skills.</p>

