<p><strong>The first item Raul Barbieri designed and submitted to Rexite was a table ashtray with a pierced cover, named Safe Tray and conceived in 1977</strong> - at that time it was still possible to smoke in closed public spaces and means of transport. <br></p>

<p class="block-img"><img src="https://prismic-io.s3.amazonaws.com/rexite/b1f129f7a131625dcbf634f0c72a8ded77115eab_01-safe-tray-04.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="750" /></p>

<p><br>They worked hard to mix together Rexite technologies, such as plastic injection molding, metal molding and cutting, and the result was outstanding. This item was made of an engineering polymer base and an aluminum grill. The perfect union for the company of Cusago: a simple, cheap item that could be easily delivered through Rexite’s means.</p>

<p>Since that first piece, <strong>they started producing several design items, all linked by a subtle leitmotiv that would be Rexite’s motto ever since: simple yet not banal, original yet not bizarre.</strong> After Safe Tray, they understood that making single items wasn’t enough, but a complete set of desk devices needed to be conceived. Therefore, Rexite joined the world of modern office and furniture tools.</p>

<p>Since then, Raul Barbieri began to plan an entire desk set, named “Babele”, composed of several items, including a letter tray, a desk pad, a pencil tray, a pencil cup, a memo pad holder and a letter rack.</p>

<p>At Rexite, designers and producers work closely together to ease their jobs: in order to create appropriate molds, Raul Barbieri had to design simple and well-refined lines, while production operators check the efficiency and practicality of the items. <strong>Dedicated teamwork between departments that aims to create perfect and efficient items. This is what Made in Italy is made of.</strong><br></p>

